events.name: Machine Learning Cloud Study Jam (NLP Track)
events.description:
We are excited to announce the first GDG Cloud KC event! Join us for our upcoming Cloud Study Jam and get hands-on experience with Machine Learning exploring the latest Google Cloud technologies. The event is limited to 20 participants and to attend you will need to RSVP by Wednesday November 13th.

The day will consist of five lab sessions focused on Natural Language Processing and lunch will be provided!

After the Study Jam, you‚Äôll receive 30-days free access to the entire Qwiklabs catalogue, so you can keep developing your skills at home. Complete all of the labs in the session‚Äôs quest, and you‚Äôll earn an additional free month of access to Qwiklabs as well as a badge for your online profile.

Bring a laptop and charger (PC, Mac or Chromebook)! The labs will run on all of the latest versions of popular browsers. For the best experience, make sure your laptop has Firefox or Chrome installed. Don‚Äôt forget your charger.

9:30am Lab 1: Cloud ML Engine: Qwik Start

upcoming.name: Leveraging Google Compute Engine for ML Workloads
upcoming.description:
Description:
Whether it is model training, inference, data preprocessing, or data scraping knowing how to leverage the compute power of Google Compute Engine is a useful skill to have. This talk will provide an introductory look at GCE with these machine learning workloads in mind.
